## Description {#details}

Class recording the (high level) <em>value</em> of a variable.

Identifies the value of the variable as a list of ValueIDNums and constant MachineOperands, or as an empty list for undef debug values or VPHI values which we have not found valid locations for. This class also stores meta-information about how the value is qualified. Used to reason about variable values when performing the second (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/debugvariable">DebugVariable</a> specific) dataflow analysis.

## Private Member Attributes

### DbgOps {#a327df730cc2c759ecf79b91b275aa2c0}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>DbgOpID LiveDebugValues::DbgValue::DbgOps&#91;MAX&#95;DBG&#95;OPS&#93;</>}>
If Kind is Def or VPHI, the set of IDs corresponding to the DbgOps that are used.

VPHIs set every <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/callingconv/#abdf8cf606905c10634e831390981b0ed">ID</a> to EmptyID when we have not found a valid machine-value for every operand, and sets them to the corresponding machine-values when we have found all of them.
